
[1]depute

   DEPUTE, v.t. To appoint as a substitute or agent to act for another; to
   appoint and send with a special commission or authority to transact
   business in anothers name. The sheriff deputes a man to serve a writ.

   There is no man deputed by the king to hear. 2 Sam. 15.

   The bishop may depute a priest to administer the sacrement.
